  <strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: For the Necromancer, no, I think what you wrote was fine. I was thinking more along the lines of vague allusions to Sauron and Morgoth. I can understand (and even agree with!) not wanting to say anything directly, but anyone who's read Tolkien -- or watched the movies for that matter -- will know about the One and Sauron. That's why I wrote the "winning the game" section the way I did. It implies there is an enemy to be beat, without naming him. A newbie who knows nothing about Tolkien would think that "enemy" was the Necromancer.... (especially as I had in the back of my head adding a line on how to check for quests, or a cross-link to the part of the doc that talks about that.) Anyway, I'm more than willing to be flexible about this, I'm just trying to shake it (well, all the Doc actually) upside down til all the foo falls out. <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
